<p><span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">The U.S. Department of Health and Human Services (DHHS) and U.S. Department of Labor (USDOL) have awarded hundreds of grants for healthcare training opportunities for unemployed, dislocated, and incumbent workers who want a new career in healthcare.</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">These grants are funding healthcare training projects in every state and region in the Nation.&nbsp; </span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Many grantees are community colleges, coalitions of community colleges, and hospitals and other community-based organizations that are working together to help give workforce adults new careers and opportunities in healthcare.</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Where the Healthcare Training Grant Funded Project Opportunities Are Located&nbsp; </strong></span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">These federally-funded training projects can be located by STATE; by ZIP Code; or by Community College Name and State (if the community college is the primary grantee).</span></span></p>